commit.message: Make run working directory relative to project
Fix some files not being correctly referenced in Xcode

Update SDL2 and SDL2_mixer to support arm64 (and mod playback)

I used a custom build for SDL2_mixer that includes optional support for MOD playback: https://github.com/libsdl-org/SDL_mixer/issues/419#issuecomment-1186249103
Add a docker image for Nintendo DS builds
Add a docker image for RISC OS builds

Use SDL_BlitSurface with SDL 1.2 when no scaling is required

Also fixed use of logical palettes, which is needed for this to work.
Add option to remove FPS limit
use SDL key lookup before translating to actual character. This fixes #11.

Revert unintended change in 3DS buttons

This change only makes sense once we update the SDL version used in the 3DS port

Apply suggestions from code review

Revert FILE_BASE_PATH change

Co-authored-by: Sergio Padrino <sergiou87@github.com>
Require setting release notes for beta builds
